    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-18T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-18T22:00:00-05:00" n="9"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/1795: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Forbes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-19T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 19, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 19—2:31
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>150. Peiping’s 599, September 19th, 2:30 a.m.<note n="14" xml:id="d9fn14">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_1">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 1</ref>.</note> Japanese newspapers
                    today published extras indicating a state of war between Japan and China. The
                    Foreign Office stated to a member of the staff that the facts seem to be a minor
                    clash between Japanese South Manchurian Railway guards and Chinese soldiers
                    growing out of damage to a section of railway track just north of Mukden, which
                    the Japanese Army has since occupied. The Japanese assure us they are determined
                    upon a peaceful settlement of whatever controversy arises.</p>
                <p>Under the circumstances I think it would be unwise to cancel voyage home and stay
                    here as such action might be misconstrued so I shall sail on <hi rend="italic"
                        >Empress of Japan</hi> this afternoon.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Forbes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
